# Niki-docAI 2.0 (Rebirth) - AI Protocol
# This file teaches AI agents (like Cursor/Trae) how to interact with the ndoc ecosystem.

# 1. Context Acquisition (Context)
# Before modifying any file, you MUST understand its context.
# DO NOT hallucinate rules or styles. Read the single source of truth.
#
# Command: `ndoc prompt --file <file_path>`
# Action: Run this command to get the full context prompt for the target file.
#         It includes Global Rules (_RULES.md), Local Context (_AI.md), and Syntax Definitions.

# 2. Syntax Compliance (Language)
# You MUST follow the project's DSL defined in `_SYNTAX.md`.
#
# Core Tags:
# - @API: Public interfaces (classes/functions).
# - !RULE: Mandatory constraints. Attributes: [CRITICAL], [FORBID=tag], [REQUIRE=tag].
# - @ADR: Architecture Decision Records.
# - @TODO: Technical debt or future plans.
# - @DECISION: Record architectural decisions in code comments.
# - @LESSON: Record learned lessons in code comments.

# 3. Constraint Verification (Check)
# After writing code, you MUST verify it against the project's constraints.
#
# Command: `ndoc check <file_path>`
# Action: Run this command. If it fails, you MUST fix the violations before finishing.
#         Common violations:
#         - Forbidden tags (e.g., @deprecated when forbidden).
#         - Missing required tags (e.g., @author missing on critical files).

# 4. Memory Management (Hippocampus)
# If you discover new patterns or important decisions, propose them for memory.
#
# Action: Add a comment `# @DECISION: <content>` or `# @LESSON: <content>` in the code.
#         ndoc archive will automatically harvest these observations into the local `_MEMORY.md` and VectorDB.

# 5. Documentation Generation (Output)
# Do not manually edit `_ARCH.md`, `_STATUS.md`, `_MAP.md`.
#
# Command: `ndoc all`
# Action: Run this to regenerate all documentation artifacts based on your code changes.
#         This updates Architecture Overview, Status Board, and Data Registry.

# 6. Semantic Navigation (LSP)
# Use the Niki-LSP features to understand code concepts.
# Action: Hover over symbols to see their semantic context (Concept/Definition) from VectorDB.

# 7. Knowledge Distillation (Archive)
# Periodically, or when completing a major task, archive the context.
# Command: `ndoc archive`
# Action: This extracts decisions/lessons and embeds them into the VectorDB for long-term memory.

# 8. Watch Mode (Daemon)
# When performing continuous edits, ensure the daemon is running.
# Command: `ndoc watch`
# Action: This keeps the context fresh in real-time.
